03/07/2006
VIENNA, Austria -- Italian authorities have arrested a Georgian national, working with the OSCE Mission in Skopje, for suspected drug smuggling, the OSCE confirmed on Sunday (2 July).
Regional media identify him as Zurab Lomashvili.
He allegedly smuggled 20kg of heroin from Albania to Italy.
(Albanian News - 03/07/06;
OSCE Web site, Makfax, Interfax - 02/07/06)
